### ✅ 3. `CHANGELOG.md` (v0.1.0 Release Notes)

```markdown
# Changelog

## [0.1.0] - 2026-05-27

### 🎉 Initial Release: "The Archive & The LLM"

#### ✅ Features
- Terminal-based UI with command dispatch (`ls`, `cat`, `search`, `ai`, `whoami`)
- BM25 full-text search over SQLite FTS5 archive (`imperium_archive.db`)
- Local LLM inference: SmolLM-135M-Instruct on CPU (~230MB RAM)
- RAG context injection: `search` results ground `ai` responses
- Rate limiting: 30 req/min on `/api/exec` via Flask-Limiter
- Observability: Debug logs + `/health` endpoint
- Session management: `last_search` persistence for grounded Q&A

#### ⚙️ Infrastructure
- Gunicorn + gthread workers (1 worker, 2 threads for CPU efficiency)
- Flask blueprint structure ready for expansion
- Docker-ready design (Dockerfile coming in v0.2)

#### 🧪 Testing
- Syntax validation: `python -m py_compile app.py`
- Health endpoint: `GET /health`
- Rate limit smoke test included in README

#### 🔐 Security
- Session cookies hardened (`HttpOnly`, `SameSite=Lax`)
- Rate limiting prevents abuse of inference endpoint
- No external network calls during inference (sovereign by design)

#### 📚 Documentation
- Comprehensive README with demo flow
- Architecture overview in `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` (draft)
- Deployment guide in `docs/DEPLOY.md` (draft)

### 🚧 Known Limitations (v0.1)
- CPU inference latency: ~15-20s for 150 tokens (SmolLM-135M)
- Session persistence requires cookie support in client browser
- No HTTPS built-in (use reverse proxy for production)
- Model quantization not yet implemented (full float32 weights)

### 🔜 Coming in v0.2
- [ ] GGUF quantization support (llama-cpp-python) for 3x faster CPU inference
- [ ] Dockerfile + docker-compose.yml for one-command deploy
- [ ] `/metrics` endpoint (Prometheus-style counters)
- [ ] Streaming token responses (SSE) for perceived latency reduction
- [ ] Multi-user session isolation improvements

---

*Release engineered by Aaron Summers | ajsbsd@gmail.com | ajsbsd.net | Senior Systems Engineer*
